{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/vaticle/typedb-awesome/readme","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1e5d7fca-c525-5547-b1d7-ac256cf7f1ab","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-typedb-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-typedb-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome typedb awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome TypeDB <a href=\"https://awesome.re\"><img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A curated list of awesome TypeDB resources.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb\">TypeDB</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.2k</span></span></a> is a strongly-typed database with a rich and logical type system built by <a href=\"https://vaticle.com\">Vaticle</a>. TypeDB empowers you to tackle complex problems using TypeQL, TypeDB's very own query language.</p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#open-source-projects-using-typedb\">Open source projects using TypeDB</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#conferences\">Conferences</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#documentation\">Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#example-projects\">Example projects</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#blog-posts\">Blog posts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#videos\">Videos</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#client-drivers-official\">Client Drivers (official)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#client-drivers-community\">Client Drivers (community)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ide-and-editors-support\">IDE and editors support</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#community\">Community</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"open-source-projects-using-typedb\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#open-source-projects-using-typedb\" aria-label=\"open source projects using typedb permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Open source projects using TypeDB</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/kglib\"><code class=\"language-text\">KGLIB - Machine Learning with TypeDB</code></a> - KGLIB provides tools to enable machine learning with TypeDB.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-studio\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB Studio - IDE for TypeDB</code></a> - TypeDB Studio is an Integrated Development Environment for TypeDB for performing knowledge engineering.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typedb-cti\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB OSI - Cyber Threat Intelligence</code></a> - TypeDB CTI is an open source threat intelligence platform enabling threat intel professionals to bring together their disparate CTI information into one database</li>\n</ul>\n<p>and find new insights about cyber threats.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typedb-bio\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB OSI - Biomedical Knowledge Graph</code></a> - TypeDB Bio is an open source biomedical knowledge graph providing biomedical researchers an intuitive way to query interconnected and heterogeneous biomedical</li>\n</ul>\n<p>data in one single place.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typedb-loader\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB Loader</code></a> - An open-source data migrator for loading data into TypeDB at scale.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sourceplusplus/Assistant\"><code class=\"language-text\">Source++</code></a> - Open-source automated programming assistant with runtime-aware and context-aware functionality.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RasaHQ/rasa\"><code class=\"language-text\">Rasa</code></a> - Open-source machine learning framework to automate text-and voice-based conversations.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"conferences\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conferences\" aria-label=\"conferences permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conferences</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://vaticle.com/conferences/typedb-cosmos-2022\"><code class=\"language-text\">Cosmos</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLtEF8_xCPklY3P5NLSQb1SyIYLhQssxfY\"><code class=\"language-text\">Orbit</code></a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"documentation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#documentation\" aria-label=\"documentation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Documentation</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.vaticle.com/docs/schema/overview\"><code class=\"language-text\">Introduction to TypeQL</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.vaticle.com/docs/client-api/overview\"><code class=\"language-text\">Client API</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.vaticle.com/docs/studio/overview\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB Studio</code></a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"example-projects\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#example-projects\" aria-label=\"example projects permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Example projects</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-examples/tree/master/biology/catalogue_of_life\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB Examples - Catalogue of Life</code></a> - Catalogue of Life is a database of over 4.5 million currently known taxa in biology, compiled from over a hundred different sources.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>TypeDB Loader loads this enormous dataset in so we can elegantly query it with rule-based inference TypeQL queries.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-examples/tree/master/gaming/xcom\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB Examples - XCOM</code></a> - XCOM 2 is a massive sci-fi strategy game where humanity must respond to a growing alien threat. Explore data about the XCOM 2 technology tree using TypeDB and TypeQL.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-examples/tree/master/software/github\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDB Examples - GitHub</code></a> - GitHub, the site you're on right now, is a vast pool of heavily interconnected data. See this example that integrates TypeDB and TypeQL into a GUI.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"blog-posts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#blog-posts\" aria-label=\"blog posts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Blog posts</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.vaticle.com/what-is-a-knowledge-graph-5234363bf7f5\">What is a Knowledge Graph?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.vaticle.com/machine-learning-in-robotics-symbolic-ai-e5375615544a\">The Role of Machine Learning and Symbolic AI in Robotics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/knowledge-models-and-causal-diagrams\">Knowledge Models and Causal Diagrams</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/building-a-biomedical-knowledge-graph\">Building a Biomedical Knowledge Graph</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/how-roche-discovered-novel-potential-gene-targets\">How Roche Discovered Novel Potential Gene Targets with TypeDB</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/social-graphs-for-drug-development\">Social Graphs for Drug Development</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/modelling-biomedical-data-for-a-drug-discovery-kno-1\">Modelling Biomedical Data for a Drug Discovery Knowledge Graph</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/a-clinical-decision-support-system-built-with-a-kn\">A Clincial Decision Support System Built with a Knowledge Graph</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/object-recognition-and-spacial-awareness-for-a-spo\">Object Recognition and Spatial Awareness for a SPOT Robotics System</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"videos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#videos\" aria-label=\"videos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Videos</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e0lmTSb-rzY\">Introduction to TypeDB and TypeQL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9EaxwUG9vAg\">Pandora Paper Leaks With TypeDB</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oS42lN4qSJ4\">Building a Distributed Database With the Raft Replication Algorithm</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XJDr_prOp9g\">Enabling the Computation Future of Biology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ir12x5FB4s\">Ontology-Driven Modelling for Text-Mining Around Technology and Engineering</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H-Ln8YUITRw\">Using TypeDB for Content Authorisation Across the Enterprise</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JTxvJxVNSH4\">Comparing Graph Databases to TypeDB | What you can't do with graphs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uhPDohXVcjU\">Comparing SQL to TypeQL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LFgV7sCnOrE\">Comparing Semantic Web Technologies To TypeDB</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nYDi1_UaFtU&#x26;list=PLtEF8_xCPklbGuaOANOJHZ8cvbo65LN2I\">How Can We Complete a Knowledge Graph?</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"client-drivers-official\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#client-drivers-official\" aria-label=\"client drivers official permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Client Drivers (official)</h2>\n<p>List of officially supported drivers to connect with TypeDB Server.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-rust\">Client Rust</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-rust\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-java\">Client Java</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-java\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-nodejs\">Client Node.js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-nodejs\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">33</span></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-python\">Client Python</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vaticle/typedb-client-python\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">61</span></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"client-drivers-community\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#client-drivers-community\" aria-label=\"client drivers community permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Client Drivers (community)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Humans-of-Julia/TypeDBClient.jl\"><code class=\"language-text\">TypeDBClient.jl</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typedb-client-csharp\"><code class=\"language-text\">Client C#</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typedb-client-haskell\"><code class=\"language-text\">Client Haskell</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/taliesins/typedb-client-go\"><code class=\"language-text\">Client Go</code></a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"ide-and-editors-support\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ide-and-editors-support\" aria-label=\"ide and editors support permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IDE and editors support</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typeql-plugin-emacs\"><code class=\"language-text\">typeql-plugin-emacs</code></a> - Major mode that provides syntax highlighting and basic completion for TypeQL.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typeql-plugin-vscode\"><code class=\"language-text\">typeql-plugin-vscode</code></a> - Visual Studio Code support for TypeQL.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/typedb-osi/typeql-plugin-jetbrains\"><code class=\"language-text\">typeql-plugin-jetbrains</code></a> - JetBrains support for TypeQL.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"community\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#community\" aria-label=\"community permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Community</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://forum.vaticle.com\"><co